content:
Here are some of the data points or properties that may be required for the international shipping business scenario:

1. International shipping regulations and compliance requirements
2. Harmonized System (HS) code for customs clearance
3. Commercial invoice or packing list
4. Export declaration or documentation
5. Customs duties and taxes
6. International shipping carrier or provider
7. International shipping address and contact information
8. International shipping method and service level
9. International shipping cost
10. Shipment value for customs declaration
11. Shipment weight and dimensions
12. Product restrictions or prohibitions
13. Product certifications or permits
14. Incoterms (International Commercial Terms)
15. Import/export licenses and permits

Please note that the actual data points or properties required for the international shipping business scenario may vary depending on the specific needs of your business and the types of products being shipped and the destination countries involved.
